{"lemma":"شارِبَيْنِ","slug":"شارِبَيْنِ","root":"ش.ر.ب","root_slug":"ش-ر-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ر-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"شارِب","root":"شرب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":5},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n22048"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%90%D8%A8%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92%D9%86%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"drinking"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"drinker"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"moustache","examples":[{"text":"أَغَايَةُ الدِّينِ أَنْ تُحْفُوا شَوَارِبَكُمْ\nيَا أُمَّةً ضَحِكَتْ مِنْ جَهْلِهَا الْأُمَمُ\nʔaḡāyatu d-dīni ʔan tuḥfū šawāribakum","english":"Is it the purpose of religion that you should trim your moustaches? / What a nation at whose ignorance other nations laugh!"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of the verb شَرِبَ (šariba, “to drink”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n22048","headword_ar":"شَارِبٌ","root":"$rb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Drinking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a drinker:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAribuwna","text_ar":"شَارِبُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arobN","text_ar":"شَرْبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHobN","text_ar":"صَحْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAHibN","text_ar":"صَاحِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) or, accord. to ISd, (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arobN","text_ar":"شَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"people drinking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assembling for drinking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a quasi.-pl. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAribN","text_ar":"شَارِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", being like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakobN","text_ar":"رَكْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajolN","text_ar":"رَجْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uruwbN","text_ar":"شُرُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is said by IAar [and in the S] to be pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arobN","text_ar":"شَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAribN","text_ar":"شَارِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uhuwdN","text_ar":"شُهُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAhidN","text_ar":"شَاهِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arabapN","text_ar":"شَرَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also is allowable as a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAribN","text_ar":"شَارِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kafarapN","text_ar":"كَفَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAfirN","text_ar":"كَافِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$orubN","text_ar":"اَشْرُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arobN","text_ar":"شَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or it may be an anomalous pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAribN","text_ar":"شَارِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (MF:) the pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uruwb","text_ar":"شُرُوب"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurs in the saying of El-Aashà,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"huwa AlwaAhibu AlmusomiEaAti Al$~uruw\n                      \n                     \n                        ba bayona AlHariyri wabayona Alkatano"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is the giver of female singers to the drinkers, some"},{"kind":"text","text":"clad in"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"silk and some"},{"kind":"text","text":"in"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"linen"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ir~iybN","text_ar":"شِرِّيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-  [Hence, The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mustache;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defluent hair over the mouth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) or so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$awaAribu","text_ar":"شَوَارِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lh, A, K,) which is the pl., (Lh, S, Msb,) as though the sing, applied to every distinct part: (Lh:) the two [halves] are called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAribaAni","text_ar":"شَارِبَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, TA:) or, as some say, only the sing. is used, and the dual is a mistake: (TA:) accord. to AHát (Msb, TA) and AAF, (TA,) the dual is is scarcely ever, or never, used; but accord. to AO, the Kilábees say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAribaAni","text_ar":"شَارِبَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with regard to the two extremities: (Msb, TA:) and the pl., (A, K,) or, accord. to the T &c., the dual, (TA,) signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long portions"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the hair"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the two sides of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabalap","text_ar":"سَبَلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]: (T, A, K, TA:) or (K, TA)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAribN","text_ar":"شَارِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabalap","text_ar":"سَبَلَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"altogether,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K, TA,) as some say; but this is not correct. (TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tar~a $aAribu AlgulaAmi","text_ar":"طَرَّ شَارِبُ الغُلَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The mustache of the boy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young man, grew forth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) ―         -b4-  And hence, as being likened to the two long portions of hair on each side of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabalap","text_ar":"سَبَلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAribaAni","text_ar":"شَارِبَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the sword, (T, TA,) i. e. (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Two long projections"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anofaAni TawiylaAni","text_ar":"اَنْفَانِ طَوِيلَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at the lower part of the hilt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, * K, TA,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extending from the guard,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one on one side and the other on the other side of the blade,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, * TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaA$iyap","text_ar":"غَاشِيَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leathern covering of the scabbard"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being beneath them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so says ISh. (TA.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~awaAribu","text_ar":"الشَّوَارِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euruwq","text_ar":"عُرُوق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ducts"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huloquwm","text_ar":"حُلْقُوم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"windpipe"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"certain ducts"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euruwq","text_ar":"عُرُوق"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haloq","text_ar":"حَلْق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fauces"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"throat"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that imbibe the water"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saliva?"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being the channels thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and, (K,) or, as some say, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the channels of the water"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"saliva?"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haloq","text_ar":"حَلْق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fauces"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"throat"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the neck:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"certain ducts"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euruwq","text_ar":"عُرُوق"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adhering to the windpipe, and the lower parts thereof to the lungs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so says IDrd: or rather, some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the hinder part thereof"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adhering"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"watiyn","text_ar":"وَتِين"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aorta"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having tubes from which the voice issues, and in which choking takes place, and whence the saliva issues:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and those of the horse are said to be ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"certain ducts"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by the side of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awodaAj","text_ar":"اَوْدَاج"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"external jugular veins"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"where the veterinary surgeon draws blood by cutting the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AwdAj","text_ar":"اوداج"},{"kind":"text","text":": the sing. seems by implication to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAribN","text_ar":"شَارِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) Hence the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HimaArN Saxibu Al$~awaAribi","text_ar":"حِمَارٌ صَخِبُ الشَّوَارِبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An ass that brays vehemently."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Saxibu Al$~awaAribi","text_ar":"صَخِبُ الشَّوَارِبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  [A man]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a disagreeable voice:"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus likened to an ass. (A, TA.) ―         -b6-  Accord. to IAar,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~awaAribu","text_ar":"الشَّوَارِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies [also]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majaAriY AlmaA='i fiY AlEayoni","text_ar":"مَجَارِى المَا=ءِ فِى العَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which AM supposes to mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The channels of water in the spring,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"source;"},{"kind":"text","text":"not in the eye. (L, TA.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sunobulN $aAribu qamoHK","text_ar":"سُنْبُلٌ شَارِبُ قَمْحٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ears of corn becoming,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being, pervaded by the farina:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA:) or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which the grain has hardened, and nearly come to maturity."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Weakness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"feebleness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in any animal: (K, * TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a strain"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiroq","text_ar":"عِرْق"},{"kind":"text","text":") thereof; as in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niEoma AlbaEiyru h`*aA lawolaA","text_ar":"نِعْمَ البَعِيرُ هٰذَا لَوْلَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^an~a fiyhi $aAriba xawarK","text_ar":"اَنَّ فِيهِ شَارِبَ خَوَرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Excellent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most excellent, were the camel, this one, were there not in him a strain of weakness"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"feebleness"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","S","TA","K","MF","Lh","A","T"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%B4%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%A8/","headword_ar":"شَارْبان","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_48","lexicon_en":"Sultan Qaboos Encyclopedia of Arab Names (Sultan Qaboos University, 1985)","lexicon_ar":"موسوعة السلطان قابوس لأسماء العرب","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=108108#0c4ddd","body_html":"شَارْبان<br>صورة كاتبية صوتية من شَرْبان: من يتجرع الشيء؛ أو مثنى شارب، أو المر أو العنت."}]}}